TY  - JOUR
T1  - That's Our Turf! Identity Domains and Competitive Dynamics
AU  - Livengood, R. Scott
AU  - Reger, Rhonda K.
Y1  - 2010/01/01
PY  - 2010
DA  - 2010/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.35.1.zok48
DO  - 10.5465/amr.35.1.zok48
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 48
EP  - 66
VL  - 35
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We examine the effects of organizational identity on the competitive dynamics of firms. Identity increases the awareness, motivation, and capability to respond to competitors' actions within the firm's identity domain, defined as cognitive competitive space that holds psychological value for a focal firm's management. Because of the psychological and motivational importance of a firm's identity, we predict that the actions and reactions within an identity domain may not adhere to traditional economically based explanations of managerial behavior.
AB  - We examine the effects of organizational identity on the competitive dynamics of firms. Identity increases the awareness, motivation, and capability to respond to competitors' actions within the firm's identity domain, defined as cognitive competitive space that holds psychological value for a focal firm's management. Because of the psychological and motivational importance of a firm's identity, we predict that the actions and reactions within an identity domain may not adhere to traditional economically based explanations of managerial behavior.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.35.1.zok48
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.35.1.zok48
Y2  - 2026/04/24
