TY  - JOUR
T1  - Identity As Narrative: Prevalence, Effectiveness, and Consequences of Narrative Identity Work in Macro Work Role Transitions
AU  - Ibarra, Herminia
AU  - Barbulescu, Roxana
Y1  - 2010/01/01
PY  - 2010
DA  - 2010/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.35.1.zok135
DO  - 10.5465/amr.35.1.zok135
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 135
EP  - 154
VL  - 35
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Self-narratives?stories that make a point about the narrator?help people revise and reconstruct identities during work role transitions. We propose a process model in which people draw on narrative repertoires to engage in narrative identity work in role-related interactions. Using feedback from their interactions, they revise both the stories and repertoires. Successful completion of the transition is facilitated by enduring and coherent repertoire changes to express the new role identity.
AB  - Self-narratives?stories that make a point about the narrator?help people revise and reconstruct identities during work role transitions. We propose a process model in which people draw on narrative repertoires to engage in narrative identity work in role-related interactions. Using feedback from their interactions, they revise both the stories and repertoires. Successful completion of the transition is facilitated by enduring and coherent repertoire changes to express the new role identity.
